# Validation (Opus 4.6)

## Principle

**Verified facts only.** No estimates, no assumed metrics.

---

## Validation Levels

| Level | Name | Meaning |
|-------|------|---------|
| L1 | Hypothesis | Unverified, in PLAN.md |
| L2 | Sampled | Partial coverage |
| L3 | Verified | Full coverage |

---

## Rules

NEVER:
- Generate counts without query
- Hardcode metrics in code
- "Approximately", "~1M rows"
- Assume system state without checking

ALWAYS:
- Run query → show result
- State coverage %
- Mark hypotheses in PLAN.md

---

## Agent's Validation

The deployed agent has its own validation rules in
`agent_rules/core-constitution.md` (safety) and `agent_rules/runtime/autonomy.md`
(resource thresholds). When writing agent code, implement those checks as runtime logic.
